1
00:00:00,810 --> 00:00:05,010
She should be grateful
I stole her and not Oh Jang Mi.

2
00:00:05,580 --> 00:00:07,780
I'm the one
who lets her live like a princess.

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:11,850
If I had taken Oh Jang Mi instead of her,

4
00:00:12,450 --> 00:00:14,050
she'd be the one suffering...

5
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:15,650
as Jung Suk Hee's daughter
right now, right?

6
00:00:16,620 --> 00:00:18,790
I'm the one who changed her fate.

7
00:00:19,260 --> 00:00:21,560
And she repays me by running wild
with no sense of gratitude.

8
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:23,730
She really gets on my nerves.

9
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:25,460
And Jung Suk Hee...

10
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:28,600
jumped off a cliff like a fool
to save Oh Jang Mi,

11
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:29,630
and now she's not all there.

12
00:00:29,970 --> 00:00:31,600
What was the point of even surviving?

13
00:00:32,070 --> 00:00:34,410
She's just a lifelong burden
on Oh Jang Mi.

14
00:00:35,070 --> 00:00:37,810
So that woman, Suk Hee,
really is my birth mother.

15
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:40,810
Wait, she took me from a set of twins?

16
00:00:41,210 --> 00:00:44,250
That's kidnapping. Shit! She's crazy!

17
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:49,420
Seo Rin should be on her knees
thanking me.

18
00:00:50,090 --> 00:00:52,760
Otherwise, she'd struggle like Oh Jang Mi.

19
00:00:52,760 --> 00:00:53,760
What other life would she have had?

20
00:00:54,060 --> 00:00:55,560
I'll keep a close eye on Seo Rin as well.

21
00:00:55,860 --> 00:00:59,060
Seo Rin is sharper than she looks.

22
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:01,800
She could catch on quickly.
Be careful.

23
00:01:02,170 --> 00:01:05,640
Understood. I'll watch her discreetly.

24
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:09,740
So I was the twin she took
to bring to this house.

25
00:01:10,510 --> 00:01:11,910
"Be grateful?"

26
00:01:11,910 --> 00:01:13,580
She kidnapped me from my own birth mother.

27
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,080
How can she say that?

28
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:23,090
I'm a daughter of that woman,
Jung Suk Hee?

29
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:24,890
No. I hate that.

30
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:29,330
I don't want to be that fool's daughter!
Why does it have to be her?

31
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:31,930
Shit... This is infuriating.

32
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:36,100
But how on earth...

33
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,040
did Mom end up stealing me?

34
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:41,710
What did she do,

35
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:43,640
and how could something
like this even happen?

36
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,440
This is unbelievable!

37
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:47,750
Shit!

38
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:58,320
Mom, I'm heading out.

39
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:01,460
Tae Pyung is so pretty.

40
00:02:01,890 --> 00:02:05,100
Tae Pyung's making money.
Tae Pyung's going to work.

41
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,170
That new sparkly outfit
looks amazing on you.

42
00:02:09,230 --> 00:02:12,540
You got that on a payment plan,
so work hard singing to pay it off.

43
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:15,110
Don't you worry about a thing.

44
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,770
- All right, I'm off!
- Bye.

45
00:02:16,770 --> 00:02:18,680
- Break a leg!
- Let's do this!

46
00:02:44,470 --> 00:02:47,910
Was my mom really such a monster?

47
00:02:49,140 --> 00:02:52,410
You're not that kind of person,
Mom, right?

48
00:02:53,210 --> 00:02:54,210
Tell me you're not.

49
00:02:57,220 --> 00:02:58,580
The woman who gave birth to me...

50
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:03,120
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

51
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:04,420
Mom, you had a bad cold,

52
00:03:04,420 --> 00:03:06,320
but you got better right away
after taking your medicine, didn't you?

53
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:10,960
Mom, you need to make sure you bundle up
so you don't get sick again, okay?

54
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,570
Jang Mi, you're so pretty.

55
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:16,030
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

56
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:18,770
That's right. I'm your daughter, Mom.

57
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:23,810
Shit. This is so annoying.

58
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:27,980
How can a woman like that
be my real mother?

59
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:32,150
I'm going to lose my mind.

60
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:41,930
It's true that clothes make the man.

61
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:46,530
Putting on a proper stage costume
really changes my whole mindset.

62
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,670
- Okay.
- Hey, Tae Pyung.

63
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:51,470
You're not up next.

64
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:52,870
What?

65
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:55,670
Go on, break a leg.

66
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,510
Sir, I'm supposed to be next.

67
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,150
I need a word with you.

68
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:13,190
What? CEO Chae cut me off?

69
00:04:13,830 --> 00:04:16,460
Right. You're a complete amateur,

70
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:18,800
so what could I possibly do
with someone as unknown as you?

71
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,430
You're not even a proper rookie.

72
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:23,800
So all this time, you only kept me on
because of CEO Chae?

73
00:04:23,970 --> 00:04:25,240
Don't make me repeat myself.

74
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:28,670
Either way, we're done as of today.
Don't come back.

75
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:32,140
Sir, but you can't just spring this on me.

76
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:36,150
What, you want a preview
before I fire you?

77
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:38,380
Sir.

78
00:04:42,050 --> 00:04:43,250
Please, just help me out here.

79
00:04:44,460 --> 00:04:45,590
I know I can do a great job.

80
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:49,160
I even got a new costume.
I've got a whole new attitude.

81
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:53,230
Sir, just give me one more chance.
Please?

82
00:04:53,330 --> 00:04:56,370
Hey, that's enough.
I said we're done here.

83
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:57,700
Sir...

84
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:01,040
Please.

85
00:05:02,610 --> 00:05:03,610
Look, I'm paying...

86
00:05:03,910 --> 00:05:05,640
for this outfit in installments.

87
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:08,410
Just let me work until I can pay it off.

88
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:12,780
- Sir.
- What is with you?

89
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:13,850
Sir!

90
00:05:30,370 --> 00:05:32,170
What do you think you're doing here?

91
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:41,880
No, this can't be happening.

92
00:05:43,350 --> 00:05:44,350
Director Ma!

93
00:05:45,450 --> 00:05:47,350
Get a hold of yourself, will you?

94
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:56,690
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

95
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:58,160
What's wrong?

96
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:02,500
Look, you've had too much to drink.
I'll call you a cab so you can get home.

97
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:07,810
Mind your business!
I said, stay out of it!

98
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:11,080
So you're a crier when you're drunk.

99
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,940
Fine, cry your heart out then.

100
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:16,050
Fine! Mind your own business!

101
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:19,920
Nobody tells me what to do!

102
00:06:35,970 --> 00:06:39,570
Goodness! Where has she been drinking?

103
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,470
Did you two drink together?

104
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:42,610
No.

105
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,610
Oh, my, she reeks of alcohol!

106
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:48,080
General Manager Kang.

107
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:50,620
- How could you let her get this drunk?
- Excuse me?

108
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:53,180
Yeom San Wol, stay out of this. Go inside.

109
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:55,450
Who are you to be scolding him?

110
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:56,550
He's my employee!

111
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,860
This way. Hurry.

112
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:02,790
- General Manager Kang...
- This way.

113
00:07:04,730 --> 00:07:07,170
Why is Hwa Young
looking out for him like that?

114
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:14,110
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

115
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:15,710
I'm so sorry.

116
00:07:16,210 --> 00:07:19,040
I'll be sure to pay this month's rent
on time.

117
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:22,410
I couldn't run the shop
because of my father's passing.

118
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,050
I'm truly sorry.

119
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,650
Okay. Have a good day.

120
00:07:29,150 --> 00:07:31,690
Tae Pyung, when are you getting paid
from the lounge bar?

121
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:34,260
Even if you get paid,

122
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:36,030
you have to make
the payments on your costume.

123
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,500
Until you make it big, don't think about
bringing money home.

124
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,960
Just focus on your singing.

125
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:42,130
Jang Mi, you sound like his mother.

126
00:07:42,370 --> 00:07:45,000
You think I'm nagging Tae Pyung
because I don't know any better?

127
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:46,170
Just stop it.

128
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:51,210
I'm sorry,

129
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:53,610
but I got fired.

130
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:56,050
- What?
- Tae Pyung.

131
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:57,110
This is killing me too.

132
00:07:57,980 --> 00:08:00,750
Our whole family is a mess,
and now I can't even make a living.

133
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:04,820
But you're a great singer.
Why would you get fired?

134
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,820
That boss clearly doesn't know talent
when he hears it.

135
00:08:06,890 --> 00:08:11,130
Yes, Tae Pyung is a good singer.
Tae Pyung is wonderful.

136
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,800
I don't think I was fired
because I'm a bad singer.

137
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:18,440
It's because I couldn't get to the bar
with Dad in the hospital and his funeral.

138
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:20,840
They replaced me with another singer
while I was gone.

139
00:08:38,090 --> 00:08:40,290
Can't you keep your face
out of my sight, Mrs. Yang?

140
00:08:40,590 --> 00:08:42,690
Day in and day out,
you show up with that beaten-up face.

141
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,200
It's ruining my appetite.

142
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,560
I'm sorry.

143
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,200
It's hangover soup.
Eat up, and it will make you feel better.

144
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:55,310
Seo Rin, my dear.
Did something happen yesterday?

145
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:57,170
You'll ruin your stomach.

146
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,610
You need to think about your health.

147
00:08:58,710 --> 00:09:00,950
How could a young lady
who will get married soon...

148
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:02,380
come home completely wasted?

149
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:04,520
What will people think?

150
00:09:04,580 --> 00:09:06,680
Can't you figure out
why Seo Rin was drinking?

151
00:09:07,450 --> 00:09:08,650
It's because of you.

152
00:09:08,950 --> 00:09:11,020
What? Me?

153
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:13,120
Of course, Seo Rin would be upset.

154
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,760
Her one and only grandfather
is getting remarried.

155
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:21,200
Are you saying Director Ma got drunk
just because my mom is getting married?

156
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,500
Enough of this nonsense. Just eat.

157
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,170
Seo Rin, you should eat up
and feel better.

158
00:09:35,710 --> 00:09:38,080
I wonder what my Baek Ho is doing.

159
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:41,490
I need to at least get something going
with Baek Ho...

160
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:43,850
so I can try to make him jealous
or something.

161
00:09:45,090 --> 00:09:47,860
This is ridiculous.
I haven't even been able to meet him yet.

162
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:57,100
My dear daughter,
you've been through so much.

163
00:09:57,500 --> 00:10:00,140
Now that you're the chairman's daughter,

164
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,940
it's all smooth sailing from here.

165
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:06,810
I'll start looking for a good match
for you first thing tomorrow.

166
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:11,650
You need to marry smart, just like me.

167
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:13,420
Got it?

168
00:10:13,850 --> 00:10:14,950
I don't care.

169
00:10:14,950 --> 00:10:18,690
Right now, I'm only thinking
of Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

170
00:10:19,060 --> 00:10:22,460
What do you mean?
Did you hear a word I said?

171
00:10:36,310 --> 00:10:37,910
(DNA Test Result Report)

172
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,910
(Ma Seo Rin, Chae Hwa Young)

173
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:45,850
(Probability of maternal relationship
is determined to be 0.000054 percent.)

174
00:10:47,990 --> 00:10:49,620
(DNA Test Result Report)

175
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:50,790
(Copying to USB)

176
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:54,330
(100 percent complete)

177
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:57,730
(DNA Test Result Report,
Conversation Recording Files)

178
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:03,370
This is my insurance policy, just in case.

179
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,640
Insurance for just in case.

180
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,510
So, Mom wants to keep an eye on me?

181
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:11,480
Don't make me laugh.

182
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,880
I'll be the one controlling her.

183
00:11:23,150 --> 00:11:25,820
I'm sorry, what?
You're saying the investigation is closed?

184
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:28,660
This is absurd, Detective.

185
00:11:28,730 --> 00:11:30,260
What is it, Lawyer Kang?

186
00:11:30,530 --> 00:11:33,860
The case involving your father is closed.
Shouldn't you be relieved?

187
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:36,100
Of course, as his son, I'm relieved.

188
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:39,500
But you even said yourself
that something felt off about it.

189
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,540
Then you need to investigate this further.

190
00:11:42,670 --> 00:11:44,340
That's what the police are supposed to do.

191
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:49,580
Mom.

192
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:51,620
Why would you just hang up my phone
like that?

193
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,920
What do you think you're doing?

194
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:55,790
What do you mean, "something felt off?"

195
00:11:56,250 --> 00:12:00,060
Are you suggesting your father
murdered Oh Jang Mi's father on purpose?

196
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,730
- No, that's not what I meant. I just...
- Then what?

197
00:12:02,730 --> 00:12:03,960
The case is already closed.

198
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:06,660
But you said
there should be a further investigation.

199
00:12:06,860 --> 00:12:08,170
What could that mean?

200
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:12,600
You're a lawyer, for crying out loud.
Whose side are you on, anyway?

201
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:13,970
What would your father...

202
00:12:14,310 --> 00:12:16,670
possibly gain
by killing Oh Jang Mi's father?

203
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:19,110
That's true.

204
00:12:19,810 --> 00:12:21,250
If it were a murder,

205
00:12:21,810 --> 00:12:24,650
- it would mean someone had a motive.
- "Murder?"

206
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:25,780
Did you say, "Murder?"

207
00:12:26,450 --> 00:12:27,820
Are you out of your mind?

208
00:12:27,950 --> 00:12:29,750
Are you calling your father a murderer?

209
00:12:29,990 --> 00:12:31,660
That's not it, Mom.

210
00:12:32,190 --> 00:12:34,230
I trust Dad.

211
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:37,360
I know he wouldn't do something like that,
better than anyone.

212
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:40,800
Then why bring up murder?
Don't you dare say something like that.

213
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:43,500
You're not making any sense right now.

214
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,770
There's a mystery here
that I can't figure out,

215
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:50,810
and I don't know what it is.

216
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:54,250
It makes no sense that
Dad could be involved in this case.

217
00:12:54,610 --> 00:12:55,610
I'm just...

218
00:12:56,180 --> 00:12:57,880
I'm just so frustrated, Mom.

219
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:04,990
Hey.

220
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,430
I don't care
how crazy you are about some girl,

221
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:10,690
but how dare you suspect our father?

222
00:13:11,260 --> 00:13:15,230
Are you saying Dad did it on purpose
to kill Oh Jang Mi's father? Is that it?

223
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,070
I'm not suspecting Dad.
The whole situation is just weird.

224
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:20,970
Even the police said things don't add up.

225
00:13:20,970 --> 00:13:21,970
Shut up.

226
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:25,540
Oh, no.
Jun Ho, what do you think you're doing?

227
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:28,650
Baek Ho, are you okay?
What am I going to do?

228
00:13:29,050 --> 00:13:30,850
Why would you hit your brother?
Use your words.

229
00:13:31,950 --> 00:13:33,250
Baek Ho, are you okay?

230
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:37,220
Even when one son tries to paint
his father as a murderer,

231
00:13:38,290 --> 00:13:40,720
you still coddle him
and take his side in the end.

232
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:47,230
I'm a lawyer before I'm anyone's son!

233
00:13:47,770 --> 00:13:51,000
Everyone's equal before the law,
and no one should suffer an injustice!

234
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,800
That's what you taught me, Mom.

235
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:55,140
And I'm sorry, Dad,

236
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:57,780
but I just want to find the truth.

237
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,850
Baek Ho, I swear to you.
I'm not hiding anything from you.

238
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:05,050
I believe you, Dad.

239
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:07,550
It's not that I don't trust you.

240
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,590
I can't believe this kid...

241
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:19,760
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

242
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:22,830
What did you say?
They closed the case?

243
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,870
Yes, the order came from the higher-ups
to close it.

244
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:28,540
Detective Kim was disappointed too.

245
00:14:29,270 --> 00:14:31,710
I'll try talking
to the detective again tomorrow.

246
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:35,150
What power does he have?
His superiors ordered him to close it.

247
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:39,650
Anyway, thank you.
I'll find who bought the drinks.

248
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:43,550
I'll go with you.
It's better than going alone.

249
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:46,660
Just wait here for a minute.
Don't even think about going by yourself.

250
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:54,670
A great opportunity just came up.

251
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:57,470
Is that right? How big are we talking?

252
00:14:58,370 --> 00:14:59,970
It had better be a big payout.

253
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,340
Don't worry.

254
00:15:01,770 --> 00:15:04,040
We're looking at a return of
at least ten times the investment.

255
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:06,680
In that case, let's get things moving.

256
00:15:07,850 --> 00:15:10,880
Now that Oh Jang Mi's father's case
is closed,

257
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:14,550
I should focus on setting up
Seo Rin with Jun Ho.

258
00:15:15,150 --> 00:15:16,520
- Yes.
- Right.

259
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:19,760
Still no word on Choi Ha Joon,
the son of Choi Myung Chul?

260
00:15:20,660 --> 00:15:23,760
If we're going to take over Dream,
we're going to need his shares.

261
00:15:24,930 --> 00:15:26,060
I'm still looking for him.

262
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:34,100
Jang Mi, let's go see Bok Gil.

263
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:36,140
Bok Gil isn't here.

264
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:39,140
I miss him.

265
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,480
Mom.

266
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:43,210
Mom, why are you being like this?

267
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:45,180
Dad's gone. He's gone for good.

268
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,220
- You saw him die, Mom. You were there.
- Tae Sook!

269
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:51,190
What? Our dad is never coming back.

270
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:52,990
We can never see him again.

271
00:15:53,860 --> 00:15:57,460
Our dad spent his whole youth
taking care of you...

272
00:15:57,830 --> 00:16:00,930
and had a lifetime of hardship,
before he just died so meaninglessly.

273
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,900
He's never coming back!

274
00:16:05,470 --> 00:16:06,740
No...

275
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,570
- No.
- Do you have to be so cruel?

276
00:16:09,710 --> 00:16:10,970
Why are you trying to shock Mom like this?

277
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:14,210
I'm furious he suffered his whole life
because of you and Mom.

278
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:18,080
Why did Dad have to clean up Mom's messes
only to die like that?

279
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,150
Why?

280
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:22,590
That's enough.
What's that going to solve?

281
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:25,690
Do you really think
Dad would be happy to see this?

282
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:29,630
You sounded like you were a perfect son
to him when he was alive.

283
00:16:29,930 --> 00:16:31,760
You gave him the most grief, Oh Tae Pyung.

284
00:16:32,060 --> 00:16:34,160
Always running off to be a singer
and getting scammed.

285
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:37,770
Do you have any idea how much he suffered
cleaning up your messes?

286
00:16:37,940 --> 00:16:40,600
You're not one to be saying that.

287
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:44,040
Dad begged and pleaded with you
not to marry Bo Ra's father.

288
00:16:44,310 --> 00:16:46,780
You stole Jang Mi's tuition money
to elope!

289
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,850
Dad got so furious
and said he never wanted to see you again.

290
00:16:50,310 --> 00:16:53,480
Frankly, I never wanted to see you again
after that either.

291
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:56,120
What? You can't just talk like that.

292
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:57,220
Stop it, both of you!

293
00:16:59,190 --> 00:17:01,890
He's gone. Bok Gil is gone.

294
00:17:02,460 --> 00:17:04,900
Bring him back. Now.

295
00:17:05,530 --> 00:17:06,930
Bok Gil...

296
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:11,170
Mom. It's okay.

297
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:12,640
Dad...

298
00:17:13,570 --> 00:17:14,910
is just gone on a picnic.

299
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:19,110
A picnic?

300
00:17:22,110 --> 00:17:23,310
Tok Hee too?

301
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:24,720
You mean, this bunny?

302
00:17:25,980 --> 00:17:26,980
Yes.

303
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,960
Suk Hee is going too.

304
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:35,930
Suk Hee is going on the picnic too.

305
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:38,060
With Tok Hee and Bok Gil...

306
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:42,970
This is so frustrating.

307
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:46,100
I'm the one who wants to cry.

308
00:17:48,070 --> 00:17:50,970
What am I going to do about my poor dad?

309
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:53,110
Who knew he'd pass away so soon?

310
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:58,550
Dad.

311
00:18:08,890 --> 00:18:11,960
Seeing that Seo Rin came home that drunk,

312
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:14,730
something must have changed.

313
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:18,400
Did she really meet Oh Jang Mi?

314
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,370
Could that be why?

315
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:26,510
Right. I'd better find out if Seo Rin...

316
00:18:27,210 --> 00:18:28,780
really did meet Oh Jang Mi.

317
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:30,980
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

318
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:42,230
Ma'am.

319
00:18:42,630 --> 00:18:43,960
How have you been doing?

320
00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:46,160
I was worried about you, so I called.

321
00:18:46,230 --> 00:18:50,370
I'm managing, thank you for your concern.

322
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:53,440
I was thinking of stopping by your shop
to see you.

323
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:55,740
Okay.

324
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:02,310
Oh Jang Mi is my twin sister.

325
00:19:03,150 --> 00:19:04,720
The one who gave birth to me...

326
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,850
No.

327
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:09,190
The one who gave birth to the twins
is Jung Suk Hee.

328
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:12,120
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

329
00:19:12,190 --> 00:19:13,460
Mom, you had a bad cold,

330
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:15,660
but you got better right away
after taking your medicine, didn't you?

331
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:19,800
Mom, you need to make sure you bundle up
so you don't get sick again, okay?

332
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:22,400
Jang Mi, you're so pretty.

333
00:19:22,630 --> 00:19:24,970
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

334
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:27,840
That's right. I'm your daughter, Mom.

335
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:30,540
The woman was injured
while saving Oh Jang Mi,

336
00:19:30,540 --> 00:19:31,640
and it left her half out of her mind.

337
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:35,510
And I have a mother too, Chae Hwa Young.

338
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,750
(Dream Hotel Reopening Ceremony)

339
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:39,750
(Dream Hotel)

340
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:50,660
Good evening, esteemed guests.

341
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:57,700
(Genos Gene Examination Center)

342
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,800
(Probability of maternal relationship
is determined to be 0.000054 percent.)

343
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,970
(Ma Seo Rin and Chae Hwa Young do not
have a mother-daughter relationship.)

344
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:06,980
But Chae Hwa Young isn't my birth mother.

345
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:10,550
She's a kidnapper
who took me from Jung Suk Hee,

346
00:20:11,620 --> 00:20:13,050
and she's trying to kill Oh Jang Mi.

347
00:20:15,950 --> 00:20:17,590
How can something like this even happen?

348
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,790
I don't know.

349
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:30,330
Go on, try it on.
Let me see if I chose well.

350
00:20:31,570 --> 00:20:34,870
- Ma'am, why are you doing this for me?
- What do you mean, why?

351
00:20:35,470 --> 00:20:37,980
You've been so down
since losing your father,

352
00:20:38,340 --> 00:20:40,580
so I wanted to do something
to cheer you up.

353
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,150
You need to shake off
this sadness quickly...

354
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:47,420
and get back to being
your old, cheerful self.

355
00:20:48,190 --> 00:20:49,890
Your father would want that for you, too.

356
00:20:51,050 --> 00:20:52,490
Ma'am.

357
00:20:52,620 --> 00:20:54,290
What your father would have wanted...

358
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:57,290
is for you to get your bright smile back.

359
00:20:57,890 --> 00:20:58,930
So, cheer up.

360
00:20:59,830 --> 00:21:01,670
Thank you, ma'am,

361
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:05,100
but I already feel like
I'm always indebted to you.

362
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:07,700
Here.

363
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:09,540
Go on.

364
00:21:10,570 --> 00:21:12,180
Are you going to leave me
hanging like this?

365
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,440
Don't feel pressured.

366
00:21:15,710 --> 00:21:16,910
It's nothing expensive.

367
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:19,920
Then I'll gratefully accept it.

368
00:21:20,050 --> 00:21:21,280
Let me put it on for you.

369
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,130
She's just like my Seo Rin in every way.

370
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,730
Except she doesn't have the mole
behind her ear.

371
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:39,040
Anyway, judging by her expression,
she definitely hasn't met Seo Rin.

372
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,640
By the way,

373
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,510
have you settled
with the person responsible...

374
00:21:44,510 --> 00:21:46,040
for your father’s accident?

375
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:50,310
No.
I don't think I'll ever be able to settle.

376
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:53,720
Even if they claim it wasn't intentional
and it happened late at night,

377
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:56,420
from our point of view,
we suddenly lost our dad.

378
00:21:57,320 --> 00:21:58,320
It just feels so unjust.

379
00:21:59,090 --> 00:22:03,190
The case was full of suspicious things,
but the police just closed it suddenly.

380
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:07,360
- Really?
- They said a higher-up gave the order.

381
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:11,470
Someone powerful must be involved.

382
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:16,240
Otherwise, why would the detective
just drop a case with so many loose ends?

383
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:17,740
Oh my.

384
00:22:18,110 --> 00:22:20,940
- Is that what the detective told you?
- Yes.

385
00:22:21,010 --> 00:22:23,110
He said that it was odd
my dad suddenly went...

386
00:22:23,110 --> 00:22:24,550
from the Dream Hotel way out there.

387
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:26,750
Oh dear. That's true.

388
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:28,690
That is a bit strange.

389
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:31,190
On top of that, my dad's cell phone
just vanished without a trace.

390
00:22:31,460 --> 00:22:35,560
So how can the police just close the case
when nothing adds up?

391
00:22:35,930 --> 00:22:38,160
His phone is missing too?

392
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:41,570
Yes. I had just spoken with him on it.

393
00:22:42,170 --> 00:22:44,900
That was the last time
I ever spoke to him.

394
00:22:45,070 --> 00:22:48,610
That's truly heartbreaking, Jang Mi.

395
00:22:48,670 --> 00:22:52,440
I can't just let this go.
I'm going back to the accident scene...

396
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:54,480
to try and find my dad's phone again.

397
00:23:03,190 --> 00:23:05,260
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

398
00:23:11,090 --> 00:23:12,100
Oh Jang Mi.

399
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:15,170
Don't dig your own grave.
Just stay out of it.

400
00:23:16,170 --> 00:23:18,840
You won't find anything there anyway.

401
00:23:38,420 --> 00:23:41,320
Because Oh Bok Gil's phone
is right here with me.

402
00:23:51,470 --> 00:23:52,670
Dad.

403
00:23:57,110 --> 00:23:58,580
This place really is
in the middle of nowhere,

404
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,740
even the road getting here.

405
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,780
If someone wanted to harm your father,

406
00:24:01,910 --> 00:24:04,110
a place like this with no CCTV is perfect.

407
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:05,220
You're right.

408
00:24:05,850 --> 00:24:08,750
I thought there were CCTVs everywhere
in this country.

409
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:10,390
And with no houses nearby,

410
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:11,920
it'll be impossible
to find any witnesses.

411
00:24:12,060 --> 00:24:14,390
I was the last person my dad spoke to,

412
00:24:14,590 --> 00:24:17,360
so it's just so strange
that his phone hasn't been found.

413
00:24:18,060 --> 00:24:19,860
I'm going to search
every inch of this place again.

414
00:24:21,530 --> 00:24:24,030
I already searched the whole area,
hoping to find something,

415
00:24:24,430 --> 00:24:25,670
but there was nothing.

416
00:24:39,850 --> 00:24:41,320
Thank you, Baek Ho.

417
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:51,430
What are you doing?

418
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:54,230
I don't know exactly what happened here.

419
00:24:55,330 --> 00:24:57,730
But if your father's spirit
is watching over us,

420
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:01,570
I'm making an offering
to ask for his help.

421
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:06,210
Don't pour out too much.

422
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:09,150
I know, Jang Mi.

423
00:25:10,210 --> 00:25:12,820
Half a bottle of rice wine
was his limit, wasn't it?

424
00:25:19,220 --> 00:25:21,790
Father, it's Baek Ho.

425
00:25:22,830 --> 00:25:24,030
Jang Mi and I...

426
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:28,600
will see this through
and get you the justice you deserve.

427
00:25:29,630 --> 00:25:30,870
Please, don't you worry!

428
00:25:36,870 --> 00:25:39,010
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

429
00:25:43,580 --> 00:25:44,610
Baek Ho.

430
00:25:45,180 --> 00:25:48,590
I didn't get a chance
to thank you properly earlier.

431
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:51,990
I never expected you to bring
my dad's favorite rice wine...

432
00:25:52,260 --> 00:25:54,860
to the scene of the accident.

433
00:25:55,690 --> 00:25:57,460
I just wanted to pay my respects.

434
00:25:58,330 --> 00:26:01,770
He was a wonderful man to me, too.

435
00:26:02,970 --> 00:26:05,940
With everything we've been going through
since my dad's death,

436
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:07,900
my family has been too hard on you, right?

437
00:26:08,510 --> 00:26:10,240
Though you were always there for us.

438
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,540
Jang Mi.

439
00:26:13,610 --> 00:26:15,410
I know it would be shameless of me...

440
00:26:16,210 --> 00:26:18,450
to ask you to be with me at this moment,

441
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:21,650
but I am absolutely not giving up on you.

442
00:26:21,820 --> 00:26:25,560
But after getting tangled up
with your father in such an awful way,

443
00:26:27,060 --> 00:26:28,530
how could we possibly be together?

444
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:32,030
Just please don't push me away, Jang Mi.

445
00:26:33,530 --> 00:26:35,070
Just like I promised your father earlier,

446
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:37,930
I swear I'll be the one to solve...

447
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,070
the truth behind this case.

448
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:56,120
What? You're getting a thank-you gift
for CEO Chae?

449
00:26:56,290 --> 00:27:00,660
Yes. She went out of her way to visit
and gave me this lovely gift.

450
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,260
So I feel I should get her
something in return.

451
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:04,730
But I don't know what to get her.

452
00:27:04,730 --> 00:27:06,260
How about a nice designer scarf?

453
00:27:06,730 --> 00:27:08,260
It’s a thoughtful gesture,

454
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:09,570
but not so expensive
that it would feel awkward.

455
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:11,170
You think so?

456
00:27:20,780 --> 00:27:21,980
Thank you, come again.

457
00:27:24,550 --> 00:27:26,180
I'm in such a foul mood.

458
00:27:27,350 --> 00:27:29,690
Nothing seems to make me feel better.

459
00:27:30,090 --> 00:27:31,820
Shit, this is so frustrating!

460
00:28:33,250 --> 00:28:34,650
(The First Man)

461
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:36,090
Just think about it, Mom.

462
00:28:36,090 --> 00:28:38,790
I'm Ok Hee, and my sister is Tok Hee?

463
00:28:39,090 --> 00:28:42,030
So is that why you called us
Ok Hee and Tok Hee?

464
00:28:42,530 --> 00:28:44,930
Why are the police investigating CEO Chae?

465
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:47,500
Because Professor Kang caused an accident.

466
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:48,770
Professor Kang?

467
00:28:49,230 --> 00:28:52,040
Mom can never know I met Oh Jang Mi.

468
00:28:52,470 --> 00:28:56,070
I’m going to find out how Mom took me.

469
00:28:58,410 --> 00:29:00,410
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
